SIMPLE: inverted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inverted
<hw>In*vert"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Changed to a contrary or counterchanged order;
reversed; characterized by inversion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Situated apparently in reverse
order, as strata when folded back upon themselves by upheaval.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Inverted arch</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>an arch
placed with crown downward; -- much used in foundations.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Invertedly</ent>⟦br⟧
